                <head>276. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Between 4:04 and 4:24 p.m. on March 22, President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName>, Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                        >Dulles</persName>, and General <persName corresp="#p_GCAJ1"
                        >Goodpaster</persName> met with Prime Minister <persName corresp="#p_MH1"
                        >Macmillan</persName>, Foreign Secretary <persName corresp="#p_LSJSB1"
                        >Lloyd</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_DPH1">Patrick Dean</persName>.
                    (Eisenhower Library, President’s Appointment Book) No record of this
                    conversation has been found in Department of State files.</p>
            </div>
